President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of New Mexico due to severe storms, flooding, and mudslides that occurred between September 9-22, 2013. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding is available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures in various counties. Nancy M. Casper has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.